2004-05-30  Arthur van Dam <adam@cs.uu.nl>

	* spec/string.str: `newname' and `newname-shared' strategies that
	generate unique strings with user-defined prefix. The increasing
	counter that is used as postfix can be shared among various
	`newname' calls that use the same countergroup.

	newname -- use current term as prefix and groupname (i.e. each
	prefix has its own numbering starting at 0)
	newname-shared -- use current term as prefix and use a global
	counter (groupname = "")
	newname(|groupname) -- use current term as prefix and number within
	specified groupname.

	Note that uniqueness-checking occurs over any grouping or scoping,
	no previously used string (within one program run) will ever be
	returned by newname.

2004-04-28  Martin Bravenboer <martin@cs.uu.nl>

	* spec/placeholder.str: new SSL module that adds library support
	for ATerm placeholders to Stratego. 

	get-placeholder -- Returns the placeholder of an ATerm placeholder.
	make-placeholder -- Creates a placeholder.
	is-placeholder -- Checks if the current term is a placeholder.

	* test/placeholder-test.str: testsuite for placeholders.
	
